Class House

      • totalExpenditureOnFood

        public static int totalExpenditureOnFood​(int amtOfMilk,
                                         int amtOfRice,
                                         int amtOfWheat,
                                         java.lang.String companyOfMilk,
                                         java.lang.String companyOfRice,
                                         java.lang.String companyOfWheat)
        Returns the total expenditure on food by a house. Assume that all food items are being purchased by the Departmental store. Consider the prices of items from Departmental store class.However don't hard code them, use the functions to get the rates.
        Parameters:
        amtOfMilk - is an integer which represents the quantity of Milk consumed by a House.
        amtOfRice - is an integer which represents the quantity of Rice consumed by a House.
        amtOfWheat - is an integer which represents the quantity of Wheat consumed by a House.
        companyOfMilk - is a String which represents the brand/company of Milk consumed by a House.
        companyOfRice - is a String which represents the brand/company of Rice consumed by a House.
        companyOfWheat - is a String which represents the brand/company of Wheat consumed by a House.
        Returns:
        An integer which represents the total expenses done by a House on food bought from Departmental Rates.

      • basicExpenditurePerPerson

        public int basicExpenditurePerPerson​(int house_no)
        This method calculates the basic Expenditure by a house per person. The expenditure depends on the house number. If house number is a multiple of 5 then expenditure per person is 1000. If house number is not a multiple of 5 then expenditure per person is 700.
        Parameters:
        house_no - is an integer which refers to the house number.
        Returns:
        An integer whihc represents the basic Expenditure per person in a house.
